<hl>
<seg id=1> "China Stone" Discovered </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> September 1, Nanjing, (Xinhua News Agency) Professor Liu Yuyi, who is famous for his oil painting "A Wonderful Night", recently in Nanjing showed people a colorful pebble he discovered the other day-"the China Stone". </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The pebble resembles exactly like the Chinese auspicious long-life lock in size and shape. </seg>
<seg id=4> In the middle of the pebble is a very clear image of the People's Republic of China. </seg>
<seg id=5> On the top of the image, it is lower in the middle than at both sides, and with the right bottom part expanded a bit, the whole image is like a proud crowing rooster, and about its belly, separated by a "strait", is a long and narrow "Taiwan Island", and under its claws, is a round shaped "Hainan Island". </seg>
<seg id=6> Both "islands" are in the same color as the "continent". </seg>
<seg id=7> The whole picture is exactly like the territory of China. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Professor Liu said, he found the stone at Nanjing suburbs about 5 years ago. Later when he scrutinized it, he found the image of China. </seg>
<seg id=9> Meanwhile, he discovered that along the "northern border" in the image, there is a wandering huge dragon who has a pearl ball in its mouth. Above the dragon, there is an image of a Chinese Gold Bullion. In the middle of the image of china, there is a torch, which is the symbol of the forever vitality of the Chinese people. Along with its shape like a long-life lock, the above characters make up "5 resemblance". </seg>
<seg id=10> Therefore, Professor Liu names the pebble "5 resemblance China Stone". </seg>
</p>
